# Handwritten Digit Recognition using CNN

This project implements a Handwritten Digit Recognition system using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN).

## Project Description
The objective of this project is to classify handwritten digits (0â€“9) from grayscale images using deep learning techniques.

## Dataset
- MNIST Handwritten Digit Dataset
- Images size: 28x28 pixels
- 10 classes (digits 0 to 9)

Note: The MNIST dataset is loaded using TensorFlow's inbuilt dataset loader.

## Methodology
1. Load the MNIST dataset
2. Normalize and reshape image data
3. Build a CNN model
4. Train the model using training data
5. Evaluate accuracy on test data
6. Predict digits for new images

## Model Architecture
- Convolutional Layers
- Max Pooling Layers
- Fully Connected Dense Layers
- Softmax Output Layer

## Tools and Technologies
- Python
- TensorFlow / Keras
- Jupyter Notebook
- NumPy
- Matplotlib

## Result
The CNN model achieved high accuracy in recognizing handwritten digits.

## Conclusion
This project demonstrates the effectiveness of Convolutional Neural Networks in image classification tasks.
